<directions xmlns:php="http://php.net/xsl">&gt;
<step><![CDATA[Grill the whole peppers in the oven at 180°/200°, over a tray to catch the dripping liquid. (If you make a few extra you can cover them in oil and use in omelettes or just eat them with bread)]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Chop the shallots and garlic, sauté in olive oil until glistening]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Put the stock in a pot and warm it up]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Add the rice and toss a few seconds until warm and coated in the oil]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Add the wine, and let it evaporate briefly]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Add the diced apples, keep stirring until the win has reduced]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Start adding stock one ladleful at the time as per normal]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Menahwile peel the peppers, wash the core away, and chop them. Chop the remaining ingredients.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[When the risotto is done, add the chopped olives, peppers, coriander, salt and pepper. Mix in, cover.and stand for a couple of minutes]]></step>
&gt;</directions>
